---
title: BeaconLink Relay-First Networking Architecture
---

flowchart LR

    %% =====================================================
    %% External Clients
    %% =====================================================

    subgraph Clients["Clients & Operators"]

        CLI["BeaconLink CLI"]
        UI["Web Console"]
        API["Automation / API"]
        GitOps["GitOps Controller"]

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Control Plane
    %% =====================================================

    subgraph Control["BeaconLink Control Plane"]

        Gateway["API Gateway"]

        Auth["Identity & Authentication"]

        Planner["Deployment Planner"]

        Scheduler["Distributed Scheduler"]

        RelayManager["Relay Manager"]

    end

    CLI --> Gateway
    UI --> Gateway
    API --> Gateway
    GitOps --> Gateway

    Gateway --> Auth
    Auth --> Planner
    Planner --> Scheduler
    Scheduler --> RelayManager

    %% =====================================================
    %% Relay Network
    %% =====================================================

    subgraph Relay["Relay Network"]

        RelayA["Regional Relay A"]

        RelayB["Regional Relay B"]

        RelayC["Regional Relay C"]

        Routing["Relay Routing"]

    end

    RelayManager --> Routing

    Routing --> RelayA
    Routing --> RelayB
    Routing --> RelayC

    RelayA <-. Replication .-> RelayB
    RelayB <-. Replication .-> RelayC
    RelayC <-. Replication .-> RelayA

    %% =====================================================
    %% Private Infrastructure
    %% =====================================================

    subgraph Sites["Managed Sites"]

        subgraph Site1["Site A"]

            Agent1["BeaconLink Agent"]

            Runtime1["Runtime Adapter"]

        end

        subgraph Site2["Site B"]

            Agent2["BeaconLink Agent"]

            Runtime2["Runtime Adapter"]

        end

        subgraph Site3["Edge Site"]

            Agent3["BeaconLink Agent"]

            Runtime3["Runtime Adapter"]

        end

    end

    RelayA --> Agent1
    RelayB --> Agent2
    RelayC --> Agent3

    Agent1 --> Runtime1
    Agent2 --> Runtime2
    Agent3 --> Runtime3

    %% =====================================================
    %% Outbound Connections
    %% =====================================================

    Outbound["Outbound-Only Secure Connections"]

    Agent1 -.-> Outbound
    Agent2 -.-> Outbound
    Agent3 -.-> Outbound

    Outbound -.-> Relay

    %% =====================================================
    %% Event Streaming
    %% =====================================================

    subgraph Events["Bidirectional Event Flow"]

        Commands["Deployment Commands"]

        Status["Status Updates"]

        Metrics["Metrics"]

        Audit["Audit Events"]

    end

    Scheduler --> Commands

    Commands --> RelayManager

    Agent1 --> Status
    Agent2 --> Status
    Agent3 --> Status

    Agent1 --> Metrics
    Agent2 --> Metrics
    Agent3 --> Metrics

    Agent1 --> Audit
    Agent2 --> Audit
    Agent3 --> Audit

    Status --> RelayManager
    Metrics --> RelayManager
    Audit --> RelayManager

    %% =====================================================
    %% Network Principles
    %% =====================================================

    Principles["Relay-First Principles

• No Direct Control Plane Access
• Outbound Connections Only
• NAT & Firewall Friendly
• Zero Trust Communication
• Multi-Region Relay Network
• Highly Available
• Event-Driven Messaging
• Runtime Independent
• Site Isolation
• Secure by Default"]

    Principles -.-> Relay
    Principles -.-> Sites

    %% =====================================================
    %% Benefits
    %% =====================================================

    Benefits["Operational Benefits

• No VPN Requirement
• No Public Agent Endpoints
• Simplified Firewall Rules
• Horizontal Scalability
• Resilient Networking
• Edge-Friendly Architecture
• Centralized Routing
• Secure Remote Operations"]

    Benefits -.-> Outbound

